21:42.240 --> 21:47.160
its behavior falls into a discrete set of possibilities.

21:47.160 --> 21:51.800
The fundamental frequency, the first harmonic, second harmonic, et cetera.

21:51.800 --> 21:56.000
And you can calculate exactly what the frequencies are and so forth.

21:56.000 --> 22:00.280
So there's kind of an emergent nature to the discreteness.

22:00.280 --> 22:03.120
The discreteness is not built into the system.

22:03.120 --> 22:07.960
It is a feature of the solutions to the equations that govern the system in some high level

22:07.960 --> 22:08.960
way.

22:08.960 --> 22:09.960
But you can just see it pictorially.

22:09.960 --> 22:11.320
You can tell why.

22:11.320 --> 22:15.800
You can understand that it makes sense that there is, you know, the lowest note, a little

22:15.800 --> 22:20.000
bit higher note, a little bit higher note than that and so forth.

22:20.000 --> 22:28.120
That phenomenon is exactly why, in quantum mechanics, we see discrete behavior for things

22:28.120 --> 22:33.740
like the energy of radiation being given off by one of these atoms.

22:33.740 --> 22:39.840
So instead of thinking of the guitar string being tied down at both ends, think of the

