23:48.900 --> 23:51.100
But the essence of the issue is the same.

23:51.100 --> 23:56.500
There will be a lowest energy state of the electron, which is analogous to the fundamental

23:56.500 --> 24:01.500
frequency of the guitar string and that's the lowest energy the electron can have in

24:01.500 --> 24:03.000
a hydrogen atom.

24:03.000 --> 24:09.840
And then there is a next highest energy level state that has some discrete extra amount

24:09.840 --> 24:11.420
of energy.

24:11.420 --> 24:16.500
It is not the case that the electron's wave function can't do anything at once.

24:16.500 --> 24:18.920
It can vibrate in whatever way it wants.

24:18.920 --> 24:23.980
But there's a natural set of ways that it can vibrate or ways that it can sort of arrange

24:23.980 --> 24:29.260
itself around the proton and these are the ways that have definite energies and these

24:29.260 --> 24:35.500
