27:00.980 --> 27:04.500
A particle, classically, let's just think classically now, we haven't quantized anything

27:04.500 --> 27:07.220
yet, a particle has a location.

27:07.220 --> 27:12.380
As we said, it has a position, it has a velocity, that's what a particle is basically.

27:12.380 --> 27:18.620
Whereas a field is everywhere, okay, and I need to be very, very careful here, as careful

27:18.620 --> 27:25.740
as I can be, to distinguish the different conceptual things that sound very, very similar

27:25.740 --> 27:26.740
to each other.

27:26.740 --> 27:34.740
In this case, a classical field is very, very different from a quantum wave function, okay.

27:34.740 --> 27:39.020
