And Entanglement says that when you have two electrons, and let's say if you were actually

29:38.820 --> 29:42.140
even better, let's make it more clear because electrons are identical particles and that's

29:42.140 --> 29:46.180
going to get in the way of being correct sometimes here.

29:46.180 --> 29:48.220
Let's say we have an electron and a proton.

29:48.220 --> 29:50.900
So two particles, but very distinguishable.

29:50.900 --> 29:53.420
