30:49.020 --> 30:52.700
the proton at, there will be a complex number.

30:52.700 --> 30:58.140
And you ask the question, where are these two particles simultaneously?

30:58.140 --> 31:02.780
And the wave function tells you a complex number that you square to get the probability

31:02.780 --> 31:05.980
of seeing those two particles at that place.

31:05.980 --> 31:12.100
So this seems like a little detail that might not be very important, but it's actually super

31:12.100 --> 31:18.740
duper crucial here, namely that the wave function doesn't depend on space.

31:18.740 --> 31:22.900
In this case, in the case of the electron and the proton, the wave function depends on two

31:22.900 --> 31:25.100
copies of space.

31:25.100 --> 31:29.460
One copy saying where is the electron, one copy saying where is the proton.

31:29.460 --> 31:33.860
So in a very real sense, even though it sounds like a technicality, the wave function is

31:33.860 --> 31:35.580
not a field.

31:35.580 --> 31:38.740
The wave function of the universe, the wave function of the real world, the wave function

31:38.740 --> 31:43.860
that we care about when we do quantum mechanics is not a field in the same sense that the

31:43.860 --> 31:46.700
