you will see why that's true, because it comes right out of the equations.

01:45:22.740 --> 01:45:28.780
Given what you mean by mass, mass is a particular kind of potential energy that the fields

01:45:28.780 --> 01:45:34.420
can have, and there's no way to have that kind of potential energy and respect the symmetry

01:45:34.420 --> 01:45:35.420
at the same time.

01:45:35.720 --> 01:45:39.800
So there's a direct line from saying, there's a gauge symmetry to saying, and there's a

01:45:39.800 --> 01:45:41.520
massless particle.

01:45:41.520 --> 01:45:45.920
And that's beautiful and lovely, because we have the photon, which is a massless particle.

01:45:45.920 --> 01:45:48.440
We have the graviton, which is a massless particle.

01:45:48.440 --> 01:45:52.520
I know we haven't detected gravitons yet, and people get fussy about it, but if you

